## Children and adolescents:

Monotherapy and combination with insulin

• Metformin {{ drug.dosage_form }} can be used in children from 10 years of age and adolescents.

• The usual starting dose is one {{ drug.dosage_form }} of {{ drug.strength }} or {{ drug.strength }} once daily, given during meals or after meals.

After 10 to 15 days the dose should be adjusted on the basis of blood glucose measurements. A slow increase of dose may improve gastrointestinal tolerability. The maximum recommended dose of Metformin is {{ drug.strength }} daily, taken as 2 or 3 divided doses.
